  "response": "Here's a balanced analysis of potential strategic reforms for China's economic development:\n\n1. Economic Structural Reforms\n- Accelerate service sector and high-value manufacturing development\n- Reduce state-owned enterprise dominance\n- Enhance private sector innovation capabilities\n- Continue market-oriented economic policy reforms\n\n2. Innovation and Technology\n- Increase R&D investment, especially in semiconductors and advanced technologies\n- Develop indigenous technological capabilities\n- Create more supportive ecosystem for tech entrepreneurship\n- Invest in artificial intelligence, quantum computing, biotechnology\n\n3. Human Capital Development\n- Enhance education system focusing on creativity and critical thinking\n- Promote vocational training aligned with emerging economic needs\n- Attract and retain global talent\n- Address demographic challenges through workforce skill upgrades\n\n4. Financial System Reforms\n- Further liberalize capital markets\n- Improve corporate governance\n- Develop more sophisticated financial instruments\n- Enhance regulatory transparency\n\n5. Domestic Consumption\n- Strengthen social safety net\n- Increase household disposable income\n- Reduce savings rates\n- Develop modern consumer economy\n\n6. Green Economy Transition\n- Accelerate renewable energy investments\n- Develop sustainable infrastructure\n- Create economic incentives for decarbonization\n- Lead in clean technology development\n\nThese reforms require careful, strategic implementation balancing economic dynamism with social stability.",
